  "response_text": "# 8-Week Fitness & Diet Plan\n\n## PHASE 1: ASSESSMENT\n**Before starting:**\n- Consult your doctor\n- Set specific goals (weight loss, muscle gain, endurance, etc.)\n- Take baseline measurements and photos\n- Determine your daily calorie needs\n\n---\n\n## FITNESS PLAN\n\n### Weekly Schedule\n```\nMonday:    Upper Body Strength\nTuesday:   Cardio + Core\nWednesday: Rest or Light Yoga\nThursday:  Lower Body Strength\nFriday:    Full Body Circuit\nSaturday:  Cardio or Sports\nSunday:    Complete Rest\n```\n\n### Sample Workouts\n\n**Upper Body (30-40 min)**\n- Warm-up: 5 min light cardio\n- Push-ups: 3 × 10-12\n- Dumbbell rows: 3 × 10-12\n- Shoulder press: 3 × 8-10\n- Bicep curls: 2 × 12\n- Tricep dips: 2 × 10\n- Planks: 3 × 30-60 sec\n\n**Lower Body (30-40 min)**\n- Warm-up: 5 min cycling\n- Squats: 4 × 10-12\n- Lunges: 3 × 10 each leg\n- Deadlifts: 3 × 8\n- Calf raises: 3 × 15\n- Leg curls: 2 × 12\n- Wall sits: 2 × 45 sec\n\n**Cardio (20-30 min)**\n- Running, cycling, swimming, or HIIT\n- Moderate intensity: 20-30 min\n- Or high intensity: 15-20 min intervals\n\n---\n\n## NUTRITION PLAN\n\n### Daily Calorie Guidelines\n| Goal | Daily Intake |\n|------|-------------|\n| Weight Loss | Maintenance - 500 cal |\n| Muscle Gain | Maintenance + 300-500 cal |\n| Maintenance | See TDEE calculator |\n\n### Macronutrient Targets\n- **Protein:** 0.8-1g per lb bodyweight\n- **Carbs:** 2-3g per lb bodyweight\n- **Fats:** 0.3-0.4g per lb bodyweight\n\n### Sample Daily Meal Plan (2,000 cal)\n\n**Breakfast (400 cal)**\n- 3 egg whites + 1 whole egg\n- 1 cup oatmeal\n- 1 banana\n- 1 tbsp almond butter\n\n**Snack 1 (150 cal)**\n- Greek yogurt (1 cup)\n- Granola (¼ cup)\n\n**Lunch (500 cal)**\n- Grilled chicken breast (6 oz)\n- Brown rice (¾ cup)\n- Broccoli (2 cups)\n- Olive oil (1 tsp)\n\n**Snack 2 (150 cal)**\n- Protein shake with berries\n- Almonds (1 oz)\n\n**Dinner (500 cal)**\n- Salmon (5 oz)\n- Sweet potato (1 medium)\n- Asparagus (2 cups)\n- Olive oil (1 tsp)\n\n**Evening (200 cal)**\n- Casein protein or cottage cheese\n\n---\n\n## HYDRATION & SUPPLEMENTS\n\n**Water:** 3-4 liters daily (more if exercising)\n\n**Optional Supplements:**\n- Whey protein powder\n- Multivitamin\n- Creatine monohydrate\n- Omega-3 fish oil\n- Vitamin D (if deficient)\n\n---\n\n## TRACKING & ADJUSTMENTS\n\n### Weekly Check-ins\n- Weight (weigh 2-3x, average it)\n- Energy levels\n- Workout performance\n- Hunger/satiety\n\n### Adjustments (Every 2 weeks)\n- No progress? Reduce calories by 100-200\n- Too hungry? Add protein/fiber\n- Plateaued? Change exercises or increase intensity\n\n---\n\n## IMPORTANT REMINDERS\n\n✅ **Do's:**\n- Sleep 7-9 hours nightly\n- Warm up before workouts\n- Eat whole foods (80%+)\n- Stay consistent\n- Progressive overload (gradually increase difficulty)\n\n❌ **Don'ts:**\n- Crash diet\n- Skip meals\n- Ignore form/technique\n- Expect overnight results\n- Neglect rest days\n\n---\n\n**Start here, adjust as needed, and be patient. Results take 4-8 weeks to become visible.**\n\nWould you like me to customize this for your specific goals or fitness level?",
